Do you know what a #pickguard is? It's the small panel that you find on a #guitar's body, to protect it from getting scratched by the pick. Last year I was asked (among other cartoonists, illustrators and musicians) to draw on a pickguard, creating a unique piece that could be auctioned for charity purposes towards socially useful projects. Tonight they hold the acution and launch of the second edition of this initiative in Milan and the exhibition will stay open until November 24th. If you are around, do not miss it! Otherwise you will find more details on the page of @scratch_battipennadartista
Anyway I'm rather proud that my pickguard has been chosen for this year's exhibition poster! Here you can see what my pen has managed to create on a small piece of wood‚Ä¶

üá¨üáß No foodles today. I'm off to a #fashion event tonight so I'm sharing a fun story about Coco Chanel I discovered a while ago.
The urban legend goes that in the late 1920‚Äôs, the Duke of Westminster was so in love with #CocoChanel that he ordered to adorn all the lampposts in Westminster with her famous logo, the two crossed ‚ÄúC‚Äùs, next to his own initial: ‚ÄúW‚Äù.
Today the City of #Westminster very prosaically states that in fact the initials stand for ‚Äúcity council‚Äù and were added only in the 1950‚Äôs (but wouldn't that have  been copyright infringement?). Personally I prefer to believe the Duke of Westminster myth.
Sadly he wasn‚Äôt going to get lucky with this fancy gesture, as¬†mademoiselle¬†Chanel turned his proposal of marriage down. Somehow, despite the attempt at being romantic, I can see why‚Ä¶ üòÇ
.
üáÆüáπ Stasera vado ad un evento #modaiolo per cui ho pensato di condividere questa vecchia #leggendaurbana su #Londra e Coco Chanel: negli anni '20 il duca di Westminster era cos√¨ innamorato di Coco Chanel da far decorare tutti i lampioni di Westminster con il famoso logo con la doppia C incrociata, a fianco alla sua iniziale: W. Mito o realt√†? Ci piace crederci per poesia. Ma di sicuro sappiamo che al duca non and√≤ bene e la stilista rifiut√≤ la sua proposta di matrimonio.
